---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service — Lily"
  description="Terms of Service for Lily Care, Lily Practice, and Lily Admin platforms."
  canonical="https://www.asklily.health/terms"
>
  <main>
    <section class="page-hero" style="padding-bottom: 2rem;">
      <div class="container narrow">
        <div class="hero-eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span>Legal</div>
        <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
        <p style="color: hsl(var(--foreground) / 0.6); font-size: 0.9rem;">Effective date: January 1, 2025</p>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container narrow">
        <div class="legal-body" style="line-height: 1.75; color: hsl(var(--foreground) / 0.82);">
          <h2>1. Acceptance</h2>
          <p>By creating an account or using any Lily service, you agree to these Terms. If you do not agree, do not use the services.</p>

          <h2>2. Service Description</h2>
          <p>Lily provides a behavioral-health platform comprising Lily Care (member-facing matching and wellness), Lily Practice (practitioner practice management), and Lily Admin (organizational benefit administration). Lily is not a licensed healthcare provider and does not provide clinical services directly.</p>

          <h2>3. Accounts</h2>
          <p>You are responsible for maintaining the security of your credentials. You must be 13 or older to create an account (18 for practitioners). Provide accurate information and keep it current.</p>

          <h2>4. Acceptable Use</h2>
          <p>You agree not to: misuse the platform for non-healthcare commercial purposes; attempt to reverse-engineer or scrape the service; upload malicious code; impersonate others; or use the service in a manner that violates applicable law.</p>

          <h2>5. Payment</h2>
          <p>Organizational plans are billed per eligible employee per month (PEPM). Practitioner plans are billed monthly or via rev-share. Member access is free when sponsored by your employer, school, or health plan. All payments are processed by Stripe and subject to their terms.</p>

          <h2>6. Termination</h2>
          <p>Either party may terminate at any time. We may suspend or terminate accounts that violate these Terms. Upon termination, your data is retained per our Privacy Policy and applicable law.</p>

          <h2>7. Disclaimers</h2>
          <p>The platform is provided "as is." Lily does not guarantee uninterrupted availability. The platform is not a substitute for emergency mental health services — call 988 or 911 in a crisis.</p>

          <h2>8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p>To the maximum extent permitted by law, Lily's aggregate liability for any claim is limited to the greater of $100 or the fees you paid in the prior 3 months. We are not liable for indirect or consequential damages.</p>

          <h2>9. Governing Law</h2>
          <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania, without regard to conflict of law principles. Disputes are subject to binding arbitration in Philadelphia, PA.</p>

          <h2>10. Contact</h2>
          <p><a href="mailto:legal@asklily.health">legal@asklily.health</a></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
